host_down.body:
SOC Platform Alert
==================

Severity: CRITICAL
Alert Type: Host Unreachable
Host: {hostname}
IP Address: {ip_address}
Timestamp: {timestamp}

Details:
  Last Seen: {last_seen}
  Duration Down: {down_duration}
  Check Type: {check_type}

Recommended Actions:
  1. Verify physical/VM power state
  2. Check network connectivity
  3. Review system logs if accessible
  4. Escalate to on-call engineer if unresolved in 10 minutes

Dashboard: http://localhost:5601
Zabbix: http://localhost:8080

--
SOC Platform Phase 1 | Automated Alert

unauthorized_access.body:
SOC Platform Security Alert
===========================

Severity: HIGH
Alert Type: Unauthorized Access Attempt
Host: {hostname}
Timestamp: {timestamp}

Details:
  User: {username}
  Action: {action}
  Source IP: {source_ip}
  Rule ID: {rule_id}
  Rule Description: {rule_description}

MITRE ATT&CK: {mitre_id}

Recommended Actions:
  1. Review user activity: last {username}
  2. Check for privilege escalation attempts
  3. Audit sudo logs: grep {username} /var/log/auth.log
  4. Consider locking account if suspicious: passwd -l {username}

Kibana Dashboard: http://localhost:5601

--
SOC Platform Phase 1 | Automated Security Alert

